  "texts": [
    "It also mentions that academia distinguishes four major fields: (i) Meta-ethics, (ii) normative ethics, (iii) descriptive ethics, and (iv) applied ethics \" (EUHLEX, 2019, p. 37).",
    "Within these, AI ethics belongs to the latter group of applied ethics that focuses on the practical issues raised by the design, development, implementation, and use of AI systems.",
    "By extension, the application of AI systems in higher education also falls under the domain of applied ethics.",
    "The selection of sample universities.",
    "The collection of cases started with the AI guidelines compiled by the authors as members of the AI Committee at their university from May to July 2023."
  ]
}